article_title: 11 Million UnitedHealth Patients No Longer Fee-For-Service

article_metadata.author: Bruce Japsen

og.description: The nation’s largest health insurer, UnitedHealth (UNH), says more than 11 million people are being cared for by medical-care providers who are paid based on quality and health outcomes of patients. And that number is expected to grow rapidly as the insurer escalates by some 50% the number of contracts it [...]
